 <!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of condition evaluation data.

 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   	<li>Identification of the condition evaluated;</li>
	<li>Identification of the object being evaluated;</li>
	<li>The recording of parameter values evaluated and evaluation outcome;</li>
	<li>The recording of the result of condition evaluated;</li>
	<li>The recording of the result of criteria elements evaluated.</li>

 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   	<li>Evaluation of objects not identifiable by an ISO 10303 specified entity and its associated identifier;</li>	
   	<li>The computation or conversion of parameter values;</li>
	<li>Parameter values directly from physical signals;</li>
	<li>Identification and access of objects implied by a class hierarchy.</li>

 </outscope>

